id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY
type: component
owner: developer
extends:
  business: AIC-COMPILE-001
  language: aic-python-guidelines

component: CompileCommand
file: python/compile/CompileCommand/compile_command.py

implementation:
  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY-I1
    intent: |
      Entry point is a Click command function named compile_component().
      Named compile_component not compile to avoid Python builtin conflict.
      Accepts:
        component_name: str     ← positional, required
        --target: str           ← required, format: language or language@version
        --force: bool           ← optional flag, default False
        --verify: bool          ← optional flag, default False
      Parses target into language and optional version strings.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY-I2
    intent: |
      Target parsing:
        --target python         → language=python, version=None
        --target python@3.11    → language=python, version=3.11
        --target java@21        → language=java, version=21
      Split on @ character. If no @ version is None.
      Validate language folder exists in project root.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY-I3
    intent: |
      Config loading.
      Read .aic/aic.config.json using json.load.
      Validate provider, model, and apiKey fields are present and non-empty.
      Raise ProviderNotConfiguredError if any field is empty.
      Load API key from environment variable if value starts with ${
      Example: ${ANTHROPIC_API_KEY} → os.environ.get("ANTHROPIC_API_KEY")

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY-I4
    intent: |
      Phase 1 — Retrieval via IntentParser and InheritanceResolver.
      IntentParser reads each .intent file using yaml.safe_load.
      InheritanceResolver builds ordered context list:
        [project_intent, language_intent, module_intent, component_intent]
      Each intent loaded as a Python dict.
      Referenced standards files loaded as raw text.
      Existing generated code file read as raw text if present.
      Existing lockfile read via LockfileManager if present.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY-I5
    intent: |
      Phase 2 — Delta computation via DeltaEngine.
      Hash current component intent using hashlib.sha256.
      Compare against hash stored in lockfile.
      If hashes match — nothing changed, skip compilation, inform developer.
      If no lockfile — full generation mode.
      If hashes differ — compute delta:
        Parse old intent from lockfile snapshot.
        Parse new intent from current file.
        Identify changed behavior IDs and implementation IDs.
        Build delta dict containing only changed sections.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY-I6
    intent: |
      Phase 3 — Inference via provider adapter.
      Build prompt using PromptBuilder:
        Section 1: project standards and rules
        Section 2: language guidelines and patterns
        Section 3: business intent behaviors and journeys
        Section 4: component intent delta (changed sections only)
        Section 5: existing code file if present
        Section 6: target language and version instruction
        Section 7: explicit instruction to update only delta sections
      Select provider adapter based on config provider field.
      Call provider.generate(prompt) → returns generated code string.
      Handle provider errors explicitly — no bare except.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY-I7
    intent: |
      Phase 4 — Write and lockfile update.
      Determine output file path from component.intent file field.
      Write generated code to output path.
      Compute new intent hash.
      Create LockfileEntry with:
        component_name, language, version, intent_hash,
        provider, model, generated_at timestamp.
      Write lockfile to .aic/lockfiles/<ComponentName>-<language>.lock
      Lockfile is JSON format.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY-I8
    intent: |
      --verify flag behavior.
      After writing output file, run VerificationEngine.
      Check each declared behavior ID exists in generated code
      by searching for behavior description keywords.
      Print PASSED or WARNING per behavior.
      Log verification_passed boolean in lockfile.
      Never fail compilation on verification warning —
      developer makes final call.

  - id: AIC-COMPILE-001-PY-I9
    intent: |
      Progress output using terminal utility.
      Show spinner or step indicator for each phase.
      Phase 1: "Reading intent files..."
      Phase 2: "Computing delta..."
      Phase 3: "Calling <provider>..."
      Phase 4: "Writing output..."
      Final: "Done. <ComponentName> compiled to <language> in <time>s"

error-handling:
  - NotInitialisedError          → exit code 1
  - ComponentNotFoundError       → exit code 1
  - ProviderNotConfiguredError   → exit code 1
  - IntentParseError             → exit code 1, show file and line
  - ProviderCallError            → exit code 2, show provider error
  - OutputWriteError             → exit code 2, show path
  - LockfileWriteError           → exit code 2, warn but keep output